This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House Committee on Foreign Affairs and the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations. The letter transmits a report required by section 104(g) of the Henry J. Hyde United States-India Peaceful Atomic Energy Cooperation Act of 2006, as amended by section 105 of the United States-India Nuclear Cooperation Approval and Nonproliferation Enhancement Act of 2008. The report covers the period of October 4, 2008, to June 30, 2009, and provides an update on U.S.-India civil nuclear cooperation and developments related to India's nuclear activities. Classified information associated with these issues has been provided in a separate classified annex.